Un mélange de pas mal de pièces provenant de différents designs, dont je remercie au passage les auteurs originaux (Italianmoose et HB-3D). La construction a abouti à ce sympathique petit vaisseau qui agrémentera joyeusement une flottille de pillards du chaos ou comme soutien à des vaisseaux plus lourds dénués de chasseurs et de bombardiers.
Je pense l'utiliser avec les stats de l'Insanity, mais avec 2points de coque, 3 pour les batteries d'armes tribord et bâbord, et enfin, une batterie d'arme de proue avec arcs gauche/droite/avant d'une puissance de 2 et d'une portée de 45cm.
Bon amusement :)

Update le 13/06/25 pour corriger un bug au niveau du trou pour fixer la tige. Merci à Arthur pour cette correction

A modular set of parts for dungeon crawling in the icy void of space.


These parts use OpenLOCK clips to assemble.


You'll find the clip in the 4-Others folder.


https://www.printablescenery.com/product/open-lock/





The pieces do not use the tile system per se.





This set allows you to play games such as Space Hulk, games in the Zone Mortalis environment, Necromunda and other Warhammer 40k SF dystopian universes.





For Space Hulk players, here you'll find everything you need to redo all the missions from V1 and its expansions.


Parts will be added as we go along, enabling you to play the game's 2 expansions.


This being done on my own time, thank you for understanding my pace of adding pieces.





The squares are 33x33 mm, which is a good compromise between the volume of filament required and good playability.


The whole thing can be scaled to suit your aspirations.

Door, sleeper and bulkhead for all your space adventures, whether Space Hulk, futuristic dungeon crawler or grim dark RPG.





These pieces are part of a larger set that includes a whole series of tiles to create a modular game board. Feel free to take a look if you'd like to embark on this larger project.





You'll find 2 3MF files with supports, created with PrusaSlicer, as well as the STLs. Originally, these elements were intended for filament printing. However, the parts are small enough to be considered for resin printing if desired.

INVINCIBLE CLASS FAST BATTLESHIP


More than a cruiser but less than a battleship.


Nevertheless, it's great fun to play despite the fact that it can blow up in your face pretty quickly.


This is not an original creation, but a "Frankenstein" ship created from several kits and bits found here and there.


Thanks to the many creators who made it possible to tinker with this somewhat overlooked and underrated ship.


The version offered here is equipped with a Nova cannon, which should make this ship quite formidable despite these weaknesses.


I haven't printed it yet, a make will follow soon as soon as the file is printed.


If you have any problems, please don't hesitate to contact me.

In the heat of battle, it's sometimes necessary to salvage enemy equipment, even wreckage, and recondition it to make it usable again, and why not use your own damaged ships to reassemble everything into something usable.


That's what's on offer here. The Magos of the Dark Mechanicum always take great pleasure in corrupting and reusing imperial technology so that they can use it against the imperium.





The design isn't mine, it's a kitbash of several parts from Italianmoose for the hulls and Keiler for the turrets.





A 2.00mm slot is provided for fixing it to a base with a rod of any kind.





I haven't printed it yet, but a make will be posted as soon as possible.

A frigate that can be used as a proxy for the Firestorm frigate.


The hull design is mine, the weapon batteries and turrets are attributed to Italianmoose. Not wanting to reinvent hot water, and his designs being super cool, I simply took them over and integrated them.


I thank him for being my source of inspiration.


The design is a little larger than the original and can serve as an escort cruiser, a type of vessel between the frigate and Dauntless-type cruisers.





The file has been print-tested, with no particular problems.





An improved version was submitted following this first print run.





22/04/25


Addition of a torpedo version ship file
